c: 4
v: 78
t: "Wherever you may be, death will overtake you - even though you be in towers raised high. \"Yet, when a good thing happens to them, some [people] say, \"This is from God,\" whereas when evil befalls them, they say, \"This is from thee [O fellowman]!” Say: \"All is from God.\" What, then, is amiss with these people that they are in no wise near to grasping the truth of what they are told"